   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>New Life Lessons, Vol. 1 CONTENTS</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Assurance of Salvation</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Prayer</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Reading the Bible</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Meeting</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Preaching the Gospel</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>PREFACE</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Praise the Lord!</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>You are now saved.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>This surely is the most important thing in your life.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>You have believed and are baptized.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Now you have the life of God and are a beloved child of God.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>From now on this new life will be in you forever.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>It will enable you to live out a life full of grace and reality.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The new life that is in you is like a seed that is sown into the ground.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>It has sprouted, but now it needs to grow, develop, blossom, and bear fruit before it will express all the riches of the life of God.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>However, this process of growth requires time and care in watering and cultivating.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>For this purpose we have selected the most important basic truths in the Bible and compiled them into a series of New Life Lessons.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>These lessons introduce to the new believers the keys to the Christian life and living in a simple, concise, and step-by-step way, with the intention that they will render new believers the proper guidance and help.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>We have the assurance that if you read through these lessons carefully and practice them diligently, you will know this new life more accurately and deeply.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>In this way, youwill live out a new life that is both spontaneous and overflowing, and will lay a good foundation for the future.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>There are ten lessons in this series of New Life Lessons.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>They are:</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>1 Assurance of Salvation</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>2 Prayer</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>3 Reading the Bible</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>4 Meeting</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>5 Preaching the Gospel</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>6 Fellowshipping with the Lord</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>7 Consecration</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>8 Living in the Spirit</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>9 Experiencing Christ</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>10 Knowing the Church</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>Every lesson is in outline form, with headings and subheadings.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>The content is mostly Scripture verses with simple explanations.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>This series of lessons may be used in new believers' meetings, and it is also quite suitable for use in small meetings or private fellowship.</S>
   </TEXT>
